Dialogue: 1,0:17:10.42,0:17:16.89,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fs11\b1\fnGeorgia\fscx72\c&H34434A&\pos(118,46.667)}Tsuwabuki Festival Literature Club Exhibit Plan
Dialogue: 1,0:17:10.42,0:17:16.89,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fs12\b1\fnGeorgia\fscx72\c&H34434A&\pos(118,89.333)}Theme: "Edible Readings"
Dialogue: 1,0:17:10.42,0:17:16.89,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\an7\blur0.3\fs6\b1\fnGeorgia\fscx72\c&H34434A&\pos(32,106)}[Main Idea]\N\NWe will introduce famous authors and books with a focus on food.\NAt the same time, we will sell or hand out snacks with short notes \Nexplaining how they relate to the content of the exhibit.\N\N[Goals]\N\NTo create an enjoyable space for guests to learn more about literature \Nand get visitors interested in the literature club.\NTo introduce guests to literary icons and famous works through the \Nnew lens of food and literature.\N\N[Outline]\N\NA stamp rally connecting all 4 displays!\N\NWe will hang big display boards on the walls with our research reports \Nand put stamp stations next to them.\N\NWe will sell or hand out snacks related to our research.\N*Hand out to children and sell to normal guests.\N\NBelow are the research topics and snacks:\N* Natsume Soseki's sugar-coated peanuts\N* Dazai Osamu's cherry pound cake\N* The cookies from Swimmy\N* Mini Castella
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.12,0:17:13.29,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,The official theme will be "Edible Readings."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.29,0:17:16.89,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use food as a common theme to \Nintroduce famous authors and literary works.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:21.32,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll also prepare snacks based on \Nthe exhibit with brief annotations
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.32,0:17:23.19,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,for sale and distribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.19,0:17:25.35,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,So we're gonna sell some and give some away?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.58,0:17:29.75,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,W-We'll give them away to little kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.75,0:17:32.00,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we give them away to everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.00,0:17:34.82,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,If we do that, we'll run out in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.82,0:17:38.28,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll give stamp cards to kids \Nin elementary school and younger?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.67,0:17:41.74,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's how we'll get them \Nto l-look at the displays.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.74,0:17:46.40,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,There will be four different displays. \NWe'll put a stamp station next to each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.40,0:17:50.78,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll save the detailed explanations for now, \Nbut Komari will handle the research displays,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.78,0:17:53.46,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll take care of the \Nsnacks and room setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.46,0:17:56.66,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds great! It's all coming together!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.02,0:17:59.37,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just need an advisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.01,0:18:01.93,Default,Konuki,0000,0000,0000,,Please excuse the intrusion, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.25,0:18:06.89,Default,Konuki,0000,0000,0000,,Amana-chan asked me to stop by. \NI'm the lit club's faculty advisor, Konuki Sayo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.14,0:18:10.86,Default,Konuki,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have a lovely time together, okay?
